<DOCNO> AP880225-0053 </DOCNO>
<FILEID>AP-NR-02-25-88 0244EST</FILEID>
<1ST_LINE>u i PM-Korea-Glance     02-25 0339</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Korea-Glance,0349</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>South Korea At A Glance</HEAD>
<HEAD>With PM-South Korea, Bjt</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Here are some facts and figures on South Korea:
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
   THE LAND _ A small, mountainous country about the size of
Indiana or England, South Korea occupies the southern half of the
Korean Peninsula jutting out into the Sea of Japan and the Yellow
Sea. Its only border is with North Korea, but it is ringed by
nearby China, the Soviet Union and Japan. The country of 41 million
people has hot humid summers and very cold winters.
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
   GOVERNMENT _ South Korea is a republic with a strong
presidential system under which the presidency iniates most
government programs and the prime minister and Cabinet ministers
traditionally have had little power. The unicameral National
Assembly is playing a growing role.
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
   HISTORY _ Korea's history can be traced to at least the 1st
century B.C. Small, rival kingdoms fought for control of the Korean
Peninsula over the centuries, with China often dominating the area.
Japan seized the country in 1910 and proclaimed it a province.
   U.S. and Soviet forces ended the harsh Japanese colonial
occupation in 1945, dividing the country along the 38th parallel.
South Korea and North Korea were formed and the two nations fought
the Korean War when the communist north invaded in 1950. Forces
from the United States and other nations intervened on the side of
the south as China sent troops to fight with the north and the
Soviet Union provided supplies.
   South Korea and North Korea remain bitter enemies with hundreds
of thousands of troops poised along their border. About 40,000 U.S.
troops remain in the south under a mutual defense pact.
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
   ECONOMY _ The export-fueled economy has helped transform South
Korea into one of the economic powers of Asia and allowed it to
make a remarkable recovery from the devastation of the Korean War.
South Korea exports a wide range of electronic goods, automobiles,
ships, textiles and clothing. Its main export market is the United
States.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
