<HEAD>Man Upset Over Haircut Allegedly Tries To Kill Friend</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: SUBS 2nd graf to CORRECT that Ramirez from Bayshore, sted New
York City.</NOTE>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Police today arrested a man who, upset over a
bad haircut, bashed a man over the head with an ashtray, tied him
up and set him and his apartment on fire, authorities said.
   Pedro Ramirez, 26, of Bayshore was arrested today in Suffolk
County, said Sgt. Raymond O'Donnell, a police spokesman. Charges
included attempted murder, arson, and robbery, O'Donnell said.
   Ramirez apparently went to the home of a friend on Monday,
O'Donnell said.
   The friend, whose identity was not released, gave Ramirez a
haircut and Ramirez then ``went nuts,'' O'Donnell said.
   ``He didn't like his haircut, I guess,'' he said.
   Ramirez then allegedly knocked the victim out with an ashtray,
tied him up and set the apartment on fire.
   Firefighters found the man tied to a chair with a blanket over
his head. He was taken to New York Hospital-Cornell Medical Center
with burns over 19 percent of his body.
   A hospital administrator said she could not give out any
information about his condition.
