<HEAD>Porter Named Atlanta News Editor</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Charlotte Porter, an editor on the Associated
Press General Desk in New York, has been named news editor in the
AP's Atlanta bureau.
   Carl Bell, Atlanta chief of bureau, announced the appointment
Thursday. Ms. Porter, 33, succeeds Mary Anne Rhyne, who earlier
this month was named chief of bureau in Hartford, Conn.
   Ms. Porter, who grew up in Lenoir, N.C., was graduated from
Macalester College in St. Paul, Minn., and joined the AP in
Minneapolis in 1976. She worked in the Sioux Falls and Pierre,
S.D., offices before transferring to the General Desk in 1979.
