<1ST_LINE>r w AM-Reagan-Personnel     02-25 0252</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Reagan-Personnel,240</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>President Names Officials to FAA, Other Agencies</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   President Reagan plans to nominate Barbara
McConnell Barrett of Phoenix, Ariz., as deputy administrator of the
Federal Aviation Administration, the White House announced Thursday.
   Ms. Barrett, 37, has been a partner in a Phoenix law firm since
1985. She was vice chairman of the Civil Aeronautics Board in 1983
and 1984. She is also a former corporate attorney for the Greyhound
Corp.
   The White House also announced that the president will nominate
Kenneth J. Beirne, a former executive director of the Republican
Party of Kentucky, as assistant secretary of Housing and Urban
Development for policy development and research.
   After his service in the party position in 1981, Beirne, 41,
served in a variety of positions at HUD. He has been a free-lance
writer since last year, the White House said.
   Reagan will appoint Robert B. Barker, a former executive of the
Lawrence Livermore National Laboratory, to the new position of
assistant to the secretary of defense for atomic energy.
   Barker, 48, was with the Arms Control and Disarmament Agency
from 1983 to 1985 and has been working on atomic energy matters at
the Pentagon since then. He was at Livermore for 10 years before
coming to Washington.
   Alex R. Munson, 46, of Saipan, North Mariana Islands, chief
justice of the High Court for the Trust Territory of the Pacific
Islands since 1982, will be nominated as judge of the District
Court for the Northern Mariana Islands, the announcement said.
