<1ST_LINE>r a AM-TV-NBCChanges     02-25 0211</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-TV-NBC Changes,0216</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>NBC Adds Three Drama Programs in Midseason Shuffle</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   NBC is sending ``Highway to Heaven,'' ``A Year
in the Life'' and ``St. Elsewhere'' out to pasture and adding three
hour-long dramatic series to its schedule, the network announced
Thursday.
   ``In the Heat of the Night'' will premiere as a two-hour movie
March 6 and then move into the Tuesday 9 p.m. time slot March 15,
replacing ``Hunter.''
   ``Hunter'' will move to Saturday at 10 p.m., beginning March 12,
replacing ``J.J. Starbuck,'' which is going on hiatus and may
return later.
   A second new dramatic series, ``Aaron's Way,'' premieres as a
two-hour movie March 9, and will appear on subsequent Wednesdays at
8 p.m. It replaces ``Highway to Heaven,'' which will appear at 9
p.m. on March 16, 23 and 30, and then go on hiatus.
   ``A Year in the Life,'' currently showing at 9 p.m. Wednesday,
will be seen at 10 p.m. March 9, 16 and 23. That time slot will be
taken over March 30 by a returning series, ``The Bronx Zoo.''
   The network said it also intends to adds two comedies, ``The
Days and Nights of Molly Dodd'' and ``Beverly Hills Buntz,'' to the
schedule, but those times will be announced later.
</TEXT>
