<2ND_LINE>AM-Baby Traded,0177</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Couple Arrested For Allegedly Trying To Trade Baby For Car</HEAD>
<DATELINE>FORT WORTH, Texas (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A man and woman were charged Thursday
with trying to sell their 3-month-old baby girl after they
allegedly offered to trade the child for a car to drive to Mexico,
authorities said.
   A car lot worker told police that the woman said she and the man
wanted to trade the baby for an ``old junker'' to go to Mexico
because they could not afford to keep the baby.
   Detective Kevin Foster said Alicia Rodriguez, 31, and Porfirio
Noriega, 23, both of Fort Worth, were charged with the sale or
purchase of a child. They were held in the Tarrant County Jail in
lieu of $1,000 bond.
   A man and woman at the car dealership refused to make a trade
for the child, Foster said, but did offer to adopt the baby and
sell the couple a car on credit.
   The child is in the care of the Department of Human Services,
Foster said.
