<1ST_LINE>r a AM-SchoolShooting     02-25 0320</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-School Shooting,0330</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Police Say One Student Shot Another Outside High School</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By KIMBERLY M. SHEARIN</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>BRISTOL, R.I. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A student was shot in the head and
critically wounded by another male student Thursday in a courtyard
of Bristol High School, police and hospital officials said.
   According to witnesses, the victim was shot while pulling off
his jacket to fight with the other student, said Mike Slocum, a
senior at the school.
   The two youths had been fighting for weeks, said Kate Meyer, a
freshman.
   The 15-year-old was in critical condition with a single gunshot
wound in the head and was taken into surgery at Rhode Island
Hospital, said spokesman Rick Piester.
   Police Detective Richard Almeida said the shooting took place in
a school courtyard shortly after noon. Authorities reportedly had
at least one suspect in custody and have recovered a small-caliber
handgun.
   Neither Almeida nor Superintendent Gerald P. Bourgeois could
furnish the identities of either the shooting victim or suspect.
   Slocum said about 30 people were in the courtyard when the
shooting occurred.
   Several students interviewed said they did not witness the
shooting but saw the victim sprawled on the floor seconds later.
   Gloria Meola, a freshman, described herself as a close friend of
the victim. ``I saw him lying on the floor ... all that blood,''
she said, wincing. ``I saw him on that floor, and I freaked out.''
   Meola said the suspect ran into the school and, with the help of
another student, escaped through a window.
   Slocum and several other students described the shooting suspect
as a student who was frequently teased. ``The truth is, he was a
geek,'' he said.
   Meola said that after the shooting Principal Edward L. Jawor
told students over the intercom not to talk to reporters, ``like
we're going to act like it's a normal day and our close friend just
got shot in the head.''
</TEXT>
