<HEAD>Women Handcuffed in Practical Joke Learn Police Don't Have the Key</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SPOKANE, Wash. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Two women handcuffed together in a
practical joke had to search the city for the prankster when police
couldn't unlock the cuffs.
   Ann Bishop, 53, and her cuffmate, Stephanie Henson, 30, showed
up at the Public Safety Building close to midnight Monday, seeking
release from the cuffs.
