knew what was happening,'' Ms. Bishop said.
   After police determined they were unable to unlock the cuffs,
the women hit the streets to find Skog, she said.
   ``We found him down at Perkins (restaurant) having some coffee
and talked him into setting us free,'' Ms. Bishop said. ``Now we
are going to have to think of something really good for him. We'll
get him back.''
