<HEAD>Baker Reportedly Satisfied With Dollar-Yen Exchange Rates</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SEOUL, South Korea (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   U.S. Treasury Secretary James Baker
said Thursday he was satisfied with the current exchange rates
between the dollar and the Japanese yen, according to Japanese
officials in Seoul.
   Baker reportedly expressed that view when he met with Japanese
Prime Minister Noboru Takeshita in Seoul Thursday. Both were
attending the inauguration of South Korean President Roh Tae-woo.
   ``Efforts to stabilize the exchange rates have been
successful,'' a Japanese Foreign Ministry official quoted Baker as
telling Takeshita.
   The official, Haraguchi Koichi, said Baker predicted that the
slumping U.S. economy would recover soon and grow at least 2.5
percent this year.
