<HEAD>Japan's Consumer Spending Up</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Japan's inflation-adjusted consumer spending rose
1.9 percent in December from a year ago, the government reported
Thursday.
   Meanwhile, the government said the nation's major retailers saw
sales climb by 7.1 percent in January over the same month last year
on the strength of clothing purchases.
   The Statistics Bureau of the prime minister's office said
December's 1.9 percent consumer spending gain compared with an
adjusted 2 percent rise in November.
   Bureau officials said the December increases came largely in the
areas of education, utilities, clothing and entertainment.
