<HEAD>London Shares Close Sharply Higher</HEAD>
<NOTE>EDS: RECASTS throughout to UPDATE with trading activity, closing
index; No pickup</NOTE>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Share prices closed sharply higher Thursday as
trading volume picked up to its best level in several weeks.
   Dealers said moderately bullish company earnings reports spurred
good buying interest by financial institutions. Price rises
accelerated further in the afternoon in response to impressive
gains in early Wall Street trading.
   ``The momentum is very strong,'' a dealer said.
   At the close, the Financial Times-Stock Exchange 100-share index
was up 22.3 points, or 1.27 percent, at 1782.4, its best level for
the day. The index opened in positive territory and rose steadily
throughout the day, picking up steam after New York began trading.
   Share prices were boosted by good earnings reports from Royal
Insurance PLC, Imperial Chemical Industries PLC and British Telecom
PLC. The results helped allay fears that companies' profitability
might have suffered significantly as a result of the October stock
crash, dealers said.
