<HEAD>Rates Fall on Five-Year Treasury Notes</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Yields on five-year Treasury notes fell in
Thursday's auction to the lowest level in a year.
   The average yield was 7.65 percent, down from 8.30 percent at
the last comparable auction on Nov. 24.
   It was the lowest rate since five-year notes averaged 6.73
percent on Feb. 25. The notes will carry a coupon interest rate of
7| percent with each $10,000 in face value selling for $9,983.90.
   A total of $7.25 billion in notes were sold out of bids
totalling $22.07 billion.
