<2ND_LINE>AM-Auto Prodn,0135</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Auto Production Down This Week</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DETROIT (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Domestic automakers were scheduled to produce
211,513 cars and trucks this week, down from last week's 219,021,
Ward's Automotive Reports said Thursday.
   Automakers produced 252,785 cars and trucks during the same week
a year ago. They were were scheduled to make 126,984 cars this
week, compared with 133,536 a week ago and 174,075 in the same week
in 1987.
   Truck production for the week was scheduled at 84,529, compared
with last week's 85,485 and last year's 78,710.
   Canadian automakers were to build 20,800 cars this week,
compared with 22,786 last week and 17,012 in the same week last
year. Canadian truck production was scheduled at 17,985, compared
with 18,385 last week and 17,886 in the same week last year.
</TEXT>
